```

Let me reconsider - the empty string `""` in the join creates `...|electronic|` becoming `...|...|` so the regex has `(?:...|)` which matches empty string. This could cause the regex to match ANY word (since every word contains an empty string). That would make many words return themselves unchanged instead of being pluralized.

```typescript
import plural from "../../../../../../../../../../../subject_repositories/plural/index.js"

describe("plural", () => {
  it("should pluralize a regular word correctly when misc regex is not supposed to match it", () => {
    // In mutated code, empty string in regex alternation causes the pattern to match
    // any word (empty string matches anywhere), so regular words won't get pluralized
    expect(plural("cat")).toBe("cats")
  })
